public abstract class QueryAdaptor extends Object implements Queryable

An ancestor implementation for queries with default behaviour for all methods of Queryable but submit(...).

Rules for writing descendants:

  • call initInput(input) in submit(...) to reset field values to default ( satisfied=true, errorMsg=null, actionMsg=null).
  • only test what this query is meant to check. e.g., if input==null the query should return satisfied unless it is an isNull query.
Type of input to submit()
any class;
Type of result
same as input (by default result=input)
Author:
Ian Davies - 23 Feb. 2021
